      • getText

        public static String getText​(XMLEventReader xer,
                             String closeTag)
                      throws XMLStreamException
        This will read the text contents of a tag. The assumption is that you have the cursor on the start tag then call this. It sifts through whitespace etc. until it finds actual characters, then returns. If it finds only white space, it returns the empty string.
        Parameters:
        xer -
        closeTag -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        XMLStreamException

      • toCDATA

        public static void toCDATA​(XMLStreamWriter xsw,
                           Collection collection)
                    throws XMLStreamException
        Converts a collection to a JSONArray then to a string. This is the compliment to getText(XMLEventReader, String).

        Use

        You write the start element, invoke this, then write the end element.
        Parameters:
        xsw -
        collection -
        Throws:
        XMLStreamException
